title: NASA Names Stephen Koerner as Acting Director of Johnson Space Center
description: NASA has selected Stephen Koerner as acting director of Johnson Space Center. Koerner previously served as Johnson’s deputy director. “It is an honor to accept my new role as acting director for Johnson,” Koerner said. “Our employees are key to our nation’s human spaceflight goals. I am continually impressed with what our workforce accomplishes and […]
author: Andrea Dunn

title: NASA’s X-59 Completes Electromagnetic Testing
description: NASA’s quiet supersonic X-59 research aircraft has cleared electromagnetic testing, confirming its systems will work together safely, without interference across a range of scenarios. “Reaching this phase shows that the aircraft integration is advancing,” said Yohan Lin, NASA’s X-59 avionics lead. “It’s exciting to see the progress, knowing we’ve cleared a major hurdle that moves […]
author: Dede Dinius

title: Medicines made in space set to touch down in Australian outback
description: Varda, a US firm planning to manufacture pharmaceuticals in low Earth orbit, is expecting its second test capsule to return to Earth this week

title: Intuitive Machines' lunar lander Athena set to blast off to the moon
description: A SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket is about to launch a number of missions, including a private lunar lander, a lunar satellite for NASA and a prospecting probe for an asteroid-mining company

title: Mars once had an ocean with sandy beaches, researchers say
description: China’s Zhurong rover finds evidence of shoreline buried deep undergroundMars may not seem like a prime holiday spot with its arid landscape and punishing radiation levels, but it once boasted beaches, researchers have found.While previous discoveries of features including valley networks and sedimentary rocks has suggested the red planet once had flowing rivers, there has been debate among scientists over whether it also had oceans. Continue reading...
author: Nicola Davis Science correspondent

title: Chance of giant asteroid hitting Earth in 2032 falls to 0.0017%
description: Asteroid 2024 YR4 had reached a 3.1% likelihood of impact but further data has rendered it negligibleIt was a discovery that led to panic-inducing headlines: a giant asteroid found to be hurtling towards Earth that, while unlikely to wipe out life, could do some serious damage.But now the world can breathe a sigh of relief. After the odds of a future collision rose earlier this year, the likelihood of an impact is now so low as to be negligible. Continue reading...
author: Nicola Davis Science correspondent

title: Shooting for the moon, Intuitive Machines to launch daring lunar lander for NASA on Feb. 26
description: Intuitive Machines is poised to launch its second lunar lander in as many years, marking a significant milestone in commercial space exploration.

title: SpaceX rolls huge Super Heavy booster to pad ahead of Starship Flight 8 launch (photos)
description: The Super Heavy booster that will fly on the eighth test mission of SpaceX's Starship megarocket is now on the launch pad. Liftoff is scheduled for Friday (Feb. 28).
